            <p>Dipolog City is the Capital City of Zamboanga del Norte and the center of trade in the peninsula. It has gained worldwide promi- nence through its bottled sardines which has become one of the major industries City’s major industries.
                A popular eco-tourism destination, Dipolog’s main attractions are the Cogon Eco-Park, a 350-hectare forest, which is 30 minutes away from the City center, the Sungkilaw Falls, and the Linabo peak which commands a breathtaking view of the Dapitan and Dipolog Cities. Sports fishing and scuba diving are also fast becoming the popular reason to visit Dipolog.</p>

            <p>Meanwhile, the City’s rich history and culture trace its roots to the Subanen and later the influx of migrants from Spain, China, Bohol, Cebu and other Mindanao provinces giving inspiration to the P’gsalabuk Festival, Dipolog’s most colorful annual festival.
                The progress of Dipolog has accelerated in recent years giving way to newly opened roads and modern buildings, more commercial banks and business establishments including hotels and restaurants. The blueprint for the city’s development plan has been laid out after a series of participatory planning workshops. Dipolog is visioning itself as A God-centered, Peaceful and Self- Reliant Supercity by the year 2030.
                Best time to visit</p>
            <ol>
                <li>1. All year round. Since Dipolog is not within the typhoon belt, it is best to visit the place anytime of the year. However, from June to October, tropical fruits like durian, lanzones, marang, rambu- tan, and mangoes are abundant.</li>
                <li>2. Summertime (March to June) is the best time to enjoy the beaches and the mountain resorts. Dipolog also celebrates its fiesta every last Saturday of May and on October 7.</li>
            </ol>
