            <h3>Dipolog City’s Must Do List</h3>
            <ol>
                <li>1. Go jogging and walking at the break of dawn or sunset time in the Boulevard</li>
                <li>2. Eat at the Food Court in the Boulevard or fresh seafoods available daily at the fish port and the public mar- ket. Go sports fishing and feast on your fresh catch.</li>
                <li>3. Buy souvenir items like the bottled sardines, nito hand woven products and fruits from the different pasalu- bong centers in the city.</li>
                <li>4. Visit the Cathedral, the P’gsalabuk circle, Sports Complex, City hall and other places that eloquently speak of the city’s rich historical and cultural heritage. Take time to join the river cruise along the scenic Dipolog river and savor the excellent buffet.</li>
                <li>5. Get yourself invited to one of the meetings of the Multi-sectoral Governance Coalition (MSGC) and experience a vibrant and active partnership between the local governments and the private sector in crafting the City’s plans and programs.</li>
            </ol>
